-- BHP, Rio Tinto Agree With Japan Steelmakers on Iron Ore Price, Nikkei Says
-- Bill Koenig
-- 2010-06-16T17:10:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/bhp-rio-tinto-agree-with-japan-steelmakers-on-iron-ore-price-nikkei-says.html

          
          
             BHP Billiton Ltd. and Rio Tinto Plc
agreed with Japanese steelmakers on iron ore prices of around
$147 a ton for the July-to-September period, Nikkei English News
reported, without saying how it got the information.  
 The increase is about 23 percent higher than the previous
quarter, Nikkei said.  
          
          


  


        